Pre-Game Insights: Cricket Ireland announced the selection of three men's T20 International squads under the leadership of batter Paul Stirling.
These squads will participate in the upcoming three-match series against Pakistan in Dublin.
Heinrich Malan, Ireland Men's Head Coach, mentioned that they have an intensive block of T20 cricket coming up this month ahead of the T20 World Cup.
Malan emphasized that they will not be treating the seven games as warmups but aiming to win as many as possible.
The squad has been gradually developed and tested over the last 18 months.
Josh Little will join the squad after his IPL stint with the Gujarat Titans.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The fixture schedule for the Pakistan T20I series includes matches on 10 May 2024, 12 May 2024, and 14 May 2024, all at Clontarf starting at 3 pm local time.
